    <para id="id7738382">Neglecting fringing, the inductance 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>L</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{L \( θ rSub { size 8{m} }  \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>will vary linearly with the air-gap cross-sectional area as shown in Fig. 8.4a. Note that this idealization predicts that the inductance is zero when there is no overlap when in fact there will be some small value of inductance, as shown in Fig. 8.2.</para>
